Package com.i2group.apollo.externaldata.edrs

Contains classes and interfaces for retrieving data directly from an external data source in a Data Acquisition project.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
IExternalDataItemRetriever A mechanism that provides direct access to data in an external data source that is identified through specified provenance information.
IExternalDataRetrievalConnector A pair of methods that an external data retrieval service calls to retrieve Items from an external data source.
 

Class Summary
ContextResultMapping A mapping that associates the results in an ExternalDataContextResults or an ExternalDataContextItemsResults with the ProvenanceGroup that contained the CardProvenance that matched them.
ExternalDataContextItemsResults A result container that contains the requested Items and ContextResultMappings that associate those Items with their CardProvenance.
ExternalDataContextResults A result container that contains a Source that contains platform-compatible XML that describes the requested items, and ContextResultMappings that associate the requested items with their CardProvenance.
 

Package com.i2group.apollo.externaldata.edrs Description
